Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
1962 completed export/import, one export every 30s. Seems fixed. Merging FSM to master and will update all chains to use master branch  as FSM merge down syncs them all fine. No doubt there are more improvemnts to be made here, but we need many days of migrates to test it is 100% working. Will try to setup something  tonight to just loop them for a week on both cluters. 
We also need to add a chain and make sure my hack to make sure chains can start notarizing actaully works, it all seems ok. Defiantly needs to be tested though.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: great progress!

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: thanks. As usual I was over thinking the solution, but there could still be possible issues due to heavy reorgs. So we will need to test that and make sure the chain wont fork. I think maybe to fix the problem of transactions getting lost due to constant reorgs, when the blocks transactions are put back into the mempool it should force broadcast them all, like when you send the transaction. This technically would prevent notartizations being lost, which will really mess with it.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: as long as they get reconfirmed I dont see any problem with it, unless the attack continues for many hours.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: The new RPC calls should also wait for notarizations rather than a single confirm like the current script is using, I think that will make it a fair bit safer, but as soon as an export happens and a notarization is lost, then there is a chance for lost coins.
